  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The Lord shall smite thee with a consumption,.... An emaciation of their bodies, either through famine or wasting diseases, whereby the fluids are washed off, and men are reduced to skin and bones: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and with a fever; a hot burning disease, which dries up the radical moisture, consumes it, and so threatens with death; of which there are various sorts, and some very pestilential and mortal Jarchi and Aben Ezra interpret it of a fire in the face, by which they seem to mean what is called St. Anthony's fire: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and with an inflammation, and with an extreme burning; either in the inward parts, as an inflammation of the lungs; or in the outward parts, as carbuncles, burning ulcers, and the like: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and with the sword; in the margin it is, \"with drought\"; so Aben Ezra interprets the word, which seems better to suit with what it is in company with; and designs either drought in human bodies, occasioned by fevers, inflammations, and extreme burnings; or in the earth, through the force of the sun, and want of rain, which render the earth barren and unfruitful, and so cause a famine: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and with blasting and with mildew; whereby the corn that is sown, and springs up, comes to nothing, being blasted by east winds, or turns pale and yellow by the mildew, and so withers away; the consequence of which is want of food, and so destruction and ruin; see Amos 4:9, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and with blasting and with mildew; whereby the corn that is sown, and springs up, comes to nothing, being blasted by east winds, or turns pale and yellow by the mildew, and so withers away; the consequence of which is want of food, and so destruction and ruin; see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Amos 4:9",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and they shall pursue thee until thou perish; follow hard after them, and come so close one after another upon them, until they are utterly destroyed. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and they shall pursue thee until thou perish; follow hard after them, and come so close one after another upon them, until they are utterly destroyed. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
